<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="Admin's Choice is a practical Linux and Unix reference for system administrators and SREs, online since 2001."
>
  <p>
    <strong>Admin's Choice</strong> is a practical Linux and Unix reference for
    system administrators, SREs, and developers. The site has been online since
    2001, and its goal has stayed the same: clear, tested, no-nonsense references
    you can actually use at the terminal.
  </p>

  <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
  <p>
    Hands-on guides and references across scheduling (cron and systemd timers),
    shell scripting, system administration, services and systemd, monitoring and
    performance, networking, DevOps tooling, Python, and security. Every
    reference aims to show real commands, real output, and the gotchas that trip
    people up — not filler.
  </p>

  <h2>How content is made</h2>
  <p>
    Commands and examples are tested on current distributions — typically Ubuntu,
    Debian, and RHEL-family systems — and each article notes the environments it
    was checked on. When software changes, we revise. Corrections from readers
    are welcome and genuinely valued; a reference is only as good as its
    accuracy.
  </p>

  <h2>Who it's for</h2>
  <p>
    Whether you're looking up cron syntax for the hundredth time, debugging a
    systemd service that won't start, or learning what <code>vmstat</code> is
    actually telling you, the aim is to get you the answer quickly and correctly.
  </p>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <p>
    Found an error, have a question, or want to suggest a topic? Use the
    <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. You can also browse everything by
    <a href="/topics/">topic</a> or see the full
    <a href="/posts/">list of posts</a>.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
